Add upstream front detection network for hours-ahead prediction

Monitors 7 upstream stations across 3 corridors to detect approaching
weather systems before they reach activity locations:

North corridor (cold front early warning):
  - KPIH Pocatello, ID (230mi, 3-6hr lead)
  - KTWF Twin Falls, ID (280mi, 4-7hr lead)
  - KOGD Ogden, UT (60mi, 1-2hr lead)

West corridor (system approach):
  - KELY Ely, NV (250mi, 4-8hr lead)
  - KENV Wendover, UT (120mi, 2-4hr lead)

Southwest corridor (pre-frontal warm flow):
  - KDTA Delta, UT (100mi, 2-3hr lead)
  - KMLF Milford, UT (150mi, 3-4hr lead)

Detection scores cold fronts, pre-frontal SW flow, and approaching
systems. Multi-station triangulation refines ETA. Signals boost
frontal and pre-frontal probability in both server and client
predictors. New ?action=upstream endpoint for client display.
